==English==
===Noun===
'''sett''' (''plural'' '''setts''')

# The pattern of a symmetrical Scottish [[tartan]]. It is specified by the thread count and is the minimum number of threads that completely defines the tartan. The tartan pattern is then created by repeating the sett in both the [[warp]] and the [[weft]] of the fabric.

====Alternative spellings====
*'''set'''

#A hole dug and lived in by a [[badger]].

